      <div type="edition" rend="break-none" xml:lang="pra-Latn">
	<div type="introduction" xml:lang="en">
	  <p>This edition is based on <ref target="bibl:N">Senart 1905-1906</ref>.</p>
	</div>
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	  sidhaṃ raño <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">gotamiputasa
	  sāmi-siriyaña-sātakaṇisa</persName> <date when-custom="7" datingPoint="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi" datingMethod="cal:regnal"><app><lem source="#N">saṃvachare</lem>
	     <rdg source="#G #AS">savachare</rdg>
	    </app> sātame 7</date> hematāṇa pakhe tatiye 3 
	  <lb n="2"/>
	  divase <app><lem source="#N">pathame</lem>
	     <rdg source="#G">padhame</rdg>
	     <rdg source="#AS">paṭhame</rdg>
	    </app> kosikasa mahāseṇāpatisa 
	   <persName key="pers:Bhavagopa">bhavagopasa</persName> bharijāya
	   mahā<app><lem source="#N">seṇāpatiṇiya</lem>
	      <rdg source="#AS">senāpatiniya</rdg>
	     </app> <persName key="pers:Vāsu">vāsuya</persName> leṇa
	   <lb n="3"/>
	   <persName key="pers:Bopaki">bopaki</persName>yatisujamāna 
	   apa<app><lem source="#N">yavasita</lem>
	      <rdg source="#AS">yavesita</rdg>
	     </app>sa<app><lem source="#N">māne ba</lem>
	      <rdg source="#G #AS">māṇasa pa</rdg>
	    </app>hukāṇi varisāṇi ukute <app><lem source="#N">payavasāṇa</lem>
	      <rdg source="#AS">payavasāne</rdg>
	     </app> <app><lem source="#N">nito</lem>
	      <rdg source="#G">nīte</rdg>
	     </app>
	   cātudi<lb n="4" break="no"/>sasa ca
	   bhikhusaghasa āvāso dato ti
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Success! On the first day of the third—3rd—fortnight of winter, in the <date when-custom="7" datingPoint="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi" datingMethod="cal:regnal">seventh—7th—year</date> of the king, the lord <persName key="pers:GpŚrīyajñaSātakarṇi">Gautamīputra Śrīyajña Sātakarṇi</persName>, the Mahāsenāpatnī <persName key="pers:Vāsu">Vāsu</persName>, wife of the Mahāsenāpati <persName key="pers:Bhavagopa">Bhavagopa</persName>, of the Kauśika family, has completed and given, as an abode to the universal saṃgha of monks, this cave which had been excavated for many years, but, after having been created by the ascetic <persName key="pers:Bopaki">Bopaki</persName>, had remained uncompleted.</p>
      </div>
